commit.message:
Update sogui.py to prevent QApplication singleton destruction issue

Without this change, the existing singleton of QApplication prevents a new window to open after a previous one has been previously closed.
This solution works and has been suggested online for PySide2 several times.

commit.message:
Correct Python install directory to be arch specific

Binary (i.e. non-pure) python modules should be installed to an
arch specific directory.
Instead of doing this manually, use the Python_SITEARCH variable
provided by the new FindPython module, available since CMake 3.12.
tests no longer segfault on Python 3.10
